      "versionNonce": 408355355,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1761130006577,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "        When you call:\n\n\n\n        you’re telling the kernel:\n\n        “Hey kernel, please pause this process until at least one of \n        these file descriptors is ready for one of the events \n        I’m interested in (POLLIN, POLLOUT, etc.), or until the \n        timeout expires.”",
      "fontSize": 24.501261328309916,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "Se4cWCVC32DdEhTZusR4o",
      "originalText": "        When you call:\n\n\n\n        you’re telling the kernel:\n\n        “Hey kernel, please pause this process until at least one of \n        these file descriptors is ready for one of the events \n        I’m interested in (POLLIN, POLLOUT, etc.), or until the \n        timeout expires.”",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
