      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1761134547944,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "    A socket becomes readable (kernel sets revents = POLLIN) when any of these happen:\n\n    - TCP data has arrived in the socket’s receive buffer (from the network).\n    - The peer has closed the connection (read returns 0 → EOF).\n    - An error occurred (e.g. connection reset).",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "Q6K5IlrL0Mjk1JbZrDK6b",
      "originalText": "    A socket becomes readable (kernel sets revents = POLLIN) when any of these happen:\n\n    - TCP data has arrived in the socket’s receive buffer (from the network).\n    - The peer has closed the connection (read returns 0 → EOF).\n    - An error occurred (e.g. connection reset).",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
