      "versionNonce": 506333319,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1761203972267,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- The kernel copies your data into the socket’s send buffer.\n\n- Then, inside kernel space, the TCP module splits the data into packets, adds headers, \nmanages sequence numbers, retransmissions, etc.\n\n- It sends them to the IP layer, then to the network driver, which hands them to the \nNIC (Network Interface Card) to put on the wire.",
      "fontSize": 7.360716333065727,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- The kernel copies your data into the socket’s send buffer.\n\n- Then, inside kernel space, the TCP module splits the data into packets, adds headers, \nmanages sequence numbers, retransmissions, etc.\n\n- It sends them to the IP layer, then to the network driver, which hands them to the \nNIC (Network Interface Card) to put on the wire.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
